subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia (
Plate 10
). Socius broad and blunt, each bearing two spines, valva simple and typical of the genus, costa strong and straight, saccus fairly long with a bulbous end. Aedeagus simple and straight, a single cornutus about one third of its length.

Female genitalia (
Plate 20
). Lamella postvaginalis with lobes close together, ostium small, ductus straight and sclerotised, corpus bursae very long and narrow, gradually widening, in all about ten times length of ductus and much the same length as abdomen.
